HEADWORD: Jesting
<hw>Jest"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Sportive; not serious; fit for
jests.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> joking.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He will find that these are no <qex>jesting</qex> matters.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jesting</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Jesting
<hw>Jest"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or practice of making
jests; joking; pleasantry.</def> <rj><au>Eph. v. 4.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jestingly</ent>⟦br⟧
